    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Big Rapids, Michigan is the perfect place for an outdoors person, with the Muskegon River running through it and several small lakes surrounding the city.  With warm, humid summers, and cold, snowy winters, there are local parks that offer golfing, bicycling, hiking, dining, shopping and sightseeing year round!  Inner tubing and canoeing on the Muskegon River is also another fun pastime to in which to partake.  Located only 45 minutes north of Grand Rapids, travelling to this larger city is a breeze.  Historic sites, lighthouses, and eleven different museums, such as the Grand Rapids Public Museum and the Gilmore Car Museum, are just a few of the attractions nearby.  With gorgeous beaches only 30 minutes away, 28 public golf areas and multiple fishing spots, Grand Rapids was rated as the #3 city in the United States for fun and recreation.  Combining an outdoor wonderland with an urban city in a fast growing region, there are theaters, large shopping centers, a range of restaurants offering different types of food, areas for dune riding, ice skating, boating, skiing, snowboarding, snowmobiling and much more!  With so much to do and see, there is no shortage of fun to be had in this small town with a big city feel!</p>
