    <h3>District Information</h3>
    <p>Recognized by the Michigan Department of Education as a Blue Ribbon Exemplary School, Big Rapids Public Schools provides students with the necessary skills to become responsible, productive and proactive citizens and members of society.  With an array of different honors and AP courses available, the district is also known for its award-winning arts and extracurricular activities, and regularly expanding these programs to ensure students will have the best of what can be offered.  With a tradition in sports that the schools are proud of, a large auditorium that can seat 575 people comfortably is available for the various athletic teams training and playing games.  In addition to the stadium, there are also two softball fields, two baseball fields, two practices fields, two soccer fields, and seven tennis courts that are local to the high school.  Developing personal skills that maximize the physical, mental, social and emotional growth of the students is the goal of all Big Rapids educators and it is evident.  While small, the Big Rapids Public Schools offer a close-knit, personalized school experience that will deliver the typical American high school experience as well. </p>
